==Graphics Data==

Enemy sprites use 3BPP (3 bits per pixel, 8 colors) format.

===Sprite Data Format===

{| class="wikitable"
! Offset !! Size !! Description
|-
| $30-$31 || word || Sprite tile data pointer (ROM address)
|-
| $32-$33 || word || Sprite palette pointer (ROM address)
|-
| $34 || byte || Sprite width (in tiles)
|-
| $35 || byte || Sprite height (in tiles)
|-
| $36-$37 || word || Animation frame data pointer
|-
| $38 || byte || Number of animation frames
|-
| $39 || byte || Animation speed/delay
|}

===3BPP Tile Format===

Each 8Ã—8 tile is stored as 3 bitplanes (24 bytes total):
* Bitplane 0: 8 bytes (bits 0 of each pixel)
* Bitplane 1: 8 bytes (bits 1 of each pixel)
* Bitplane 2: 8 bytes (bits 2 of each pixel)

Pixel values range from $0-$7 (8 colors per palette).

